    <title class="- topic/title ">Installation</title>
    <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Installation requires: 4hp available Eurorack spaces, and an ES-3 mk3/mk4, ES-8, or
        ES-9.</shortdesc>
    <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">Installation instructions differ depending on your base unit. </p>
        <p class="- topic/p ">
            <ul class="- topic/ul " id="unique_2_Connect_42_ul_ccp_nkz_sjb" nd:nd-id="ul_ccp_nkz_sjb">
                <li class="- topic/li ">House the ES-5 in a Eurorack case of your choosing. The power connector is <xref class="- topic/xref " format="html" href="http://www.doepfer.de/a100_man/a100t_e.htm" scope="external"><?ditaot usertext?>Doepfer standard</xref>. </li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Connect the power cable so "-12V" (printed on the PCB) corresponds to the red
                    stripe on the cable (see Fig.1).<fig class="- topic/fig " id="unique_2_Connect_42_fig_otn_nqp_5jb" nd:nd-id="fig_otn_nqp_5jb"><title class="- topic/title ">Fig. 1: ES-5 PCB: (L to R) to ES-3, Jumper, Ch.1-6 Expansion selectors,
                            Connection to Expander, Power</title><image align="center" class="- topic/image " href="file:/Users/CJmbP/Desktop/Dita/ES5board.jpg" id="unique_2_Connect_42_image_ptn_nqp_5jb" nd:nd-id="image_ptn_nqp_5jb" placement="break" width="532" height="308" scale="30">
                            <alt class="- topic/alt ">Fig. 1: (L to R) to ES-3, Jumper, Ch.1-6 Expansion selectors,
                                Connection to Expander, Power</alt>
                        </image></fig></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">All Units</b>
            <ol class="- topic/ol " id="unique_2_Connect_42_ol_ebr_krz_sjb" nd:nd-id="ol_ebr_krz_sjb">
                <li class="- topic/li "> Disconnect power to your Eurorack case.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Attach the power connector so "-12V" (printed on the PCB) corresponds to the
                    red stripe on the power connector (see Fig.1). <note class="- topic/note ">The red stripe must be
                        alinged with "-12V" marked on the PCB. The power connector supplied with the
                        ES-5 is keyed to in ensure a correct fit.</note></li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Connect the other end of the power cable to an available power port in your
                    Eurorack case so "-12V" on your power supply PCB corresponds to the red stripe
                    on the cable.</li>
            </ol></p>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ES-3 mk3, ES-3 mk4, ES-8, ES-9</b><ol class="- topic/ol " id="unique_2_Connect_42_ol_bpd_4vj_xjb" nd:nd-id="ol_bpd_4vj_xjb">
                <li class="- topic/li "> Disconnect power to your Eurorack case.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Connect power as instructed under "All Units."</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Connect the ES-5, with the supplied 10-way cable, to the header on your units
                    PCB (see Fig. 1 and Fig. 2).<fig class="- topic/fig " id="unique_2_Connect_42_fig_fcj_xrp_5jb" nd:nd-id="fig_fcj_xrp_5jb"><title class="- topic/title ">Fig. 2: Expansion header on ES-3mk3/mk4, ES-8, and ES-9</title><image align="center" class="- topic/image " href="file:/Users/CJmbP/Desktop/Dita/ES5Port.jpg" id="unique_2_Connect_42_image_gcj_xrp_5jb" nd:nd-id="image_gcj_xrp_5jb" placement="break" width="240" height="186" scale="30">
                            <alt class="- topic/alt ">Fig. 2: Expansion header on ES-3mk3/mk4, ES-8, and ES-9</alt>
                        </image></fig></li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Ensure all connectors are seated fully and correctly.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Secure the ES-5 in your Eurorack case with the four provided screws.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Reconnect power to your Eurorack case.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Have fun!</li>
            </ol></p>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ES3 mk2</b><ol class="- topic/ol " id="unique_2_Connect_42_ol_om1_5vj_xjb" nd:nd-id="ol_om1_5vj_xjb">
                <li class="- topic/li "> Disconnect power to your Eurorack case.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Connect power as instructed under "All Units." </li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Connect the ES-5, with the supplied 10-way cable, to the header on your ES-3
                    mk2 PCB (see Fig. 3).<note class="- topic/note ">You may find it helpful to loosen the screws that
                        attach the PCB to the module's panel while fitting the
                        cable.</note><note class="- topic/note ">The six conductors on the side of the cable with the red
                        stripe must engage with the 6-way header on the ES-3; the four unused
                        conductors hang over the small IC at the edge of the board (see Fig.
                        3).</note><fig class="- topic/fig " id="unique_2_Connect_42_fig_j2b_gzj_xjb" nd:nd-id="fig_j2b_gzj_xjb"><title class="- topic/title ">Fig. 3: Connecting to an ES-3 mk2. Notice the last four unused
                            conductors on the cable are nearest the egde of the PCB</title><image align="center" class="- topic/image " href="file:/Users/CJmbP/Desktop/Dita/ES5Stack.jpg" id="unique_2_Connect_42_image_k2b_gzj_xjb" nd:nd-id="image_k2b_gzj_xjb" placement="break" width="256" height="192" scale="80">
                            <alt class="- topic/alt ">Connecting to an ES-3 mk2. Notice the last four unused conductors
                                on the cable are nearest the egde of the PCB</alt>
                        </image></fig></li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Ensure all connectors are seated fully and correctly.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Secure the ES-5 in your Eurorack case with the four provided screws.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Reconnect power to your Eurorack case.</li>
                 <li class="- topic/li "> Have fun!</li>
            </ol></p>
        <p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ES-3 mk1</b><note class="- topic/note ">The ES-3 mk1 lacks the expansion headers of mk2 and later. However,
                it is fairly simple to solder the equivalent connections. The suggested solution is
                to use the 10-way ribbon cable provided with the ES-5 to solder one end to the ES-3
                PCB, leaving the other end with the usual connector for the ES-5 as shown in Fig.
                4.</note><ol class="- topic/ol " id="unique_2_Connect_42_ol_csg_5vj_xjb" nd:nd-id="ol_csg_5vj_xjb">
                <li class="- topic/li "> Disconnect power to your Eurorack case.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Remove your ES-3 mk1 from your Eurorack case.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Modify the suppled 10-way ribbon cable to match Fig. 4 as detailed in further
                        steps.<fig class="- topic/fig " id="unique_2_Connect_42_fig_yf5_sjk_xjb" nd:nd-id="fig_yf5_sjk_xjb"><title class="- topic/title ">Fig. 4: Modded 10-way on ES-3 mk1. </title><image align="center" class="- topic/image " href="file:/Users/CJmbP/Desktop/Dita/Images/es3mk1_mod.jpg" id="unique_2_Connect_42_image_zf5_sjk_xjb" nd:nd-id="image_zf5_sjk_xjb" placement="break" width="512" height="205" scale="80"/></fig><note class="- topic/note "> Only six of the cable's ten conductors need to be soldered to the
                        ES-3. The other four can be discarded. !!Note orientation of red
                        stripe!!</note><fig class="- topic/fig " id="unique_2_Connect_42_fig_rgr_kkk_xjb" nd:nd-id="fig_rgr_kkk_xjb"><title class="- topic/title ">Fig. 5: Unmodified ES-3 mk1 PCB.</title><image align="center" class="- topic/image " href="file:/Users/CJmbP/Desktop/Dita/Images/es3mk1_unmod_k.jpg" id="unique_2_Connect_42_image_ugr_kkk_xjb" nd:nd-id="image_ugr_kkk_xjb" placement="break" width="320" height="243" scale="50"/><note class="- topic/note ">The highlighted areas are vias (connections from one side of the PCB
                            to the other) and are the easiest points to make the connections.</note></fig></li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Solder the connections as shown in Fig. 6. In this scheme, the conductors match
                    up to the pads in Fig. 5 as follows: <ul class="- topic/ul " id="unique_2_Connect_42_ul_ojf_j2k_xjb" nd:nd-id="ul_ojf_j2k_xjb">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">1-A</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">2-D</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">3-B</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">4-E</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">5-C</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">6-F<note class="- topic/note ">The numbers 1-6 correspond to the conductors of the ribbon
                                cable, starting from the red edge as number "1" and the letters A-F
                                correspond to the vias as shown in Fig. 5.</note></li>
                    </ul><fig class="- topic/fig " id="unique_2_Connect_42_fig_k5d_vkk_xjb" nd:nd-id="fig_k5d_vkk_xjb"><title class="- topic/title ">Fig. 6: Numbers correspond to the conductors of the ribbon cable,
                            starting from the red edge as number "1"</title><image align="center" class="- topic/image " href="file:/Users/CJmbP/Desktop/Dita/Images/es3mk1_mod_closeup_k.jpg" id="unique_2_Connect_42_image_l5d_vkk_xjb" nd:nd-id="image_l5d_vkk_xjb" placement="break" width="320" height="154" scale="50"/></fig></li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Install your ES-3 mk1 to your Eurorack case.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Attach the ES-5 power connector so "-12V" (printed on the PCB) corresponds to
                    the red stripe on the power connector (see Fig.1). <note class="- topic/note ">The red stripe must be
                        alinged with "-12V" marked on the PCB. The power connector supplied with the
                        ES-5 is keyed to in ensure a correct fit.</note></li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Connect the other end of the power cable to an available power port in your
                    Eurorack case so "-12V" on your power supply PCB corresponds to the red stripe
                    on the cable.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Connect the ES-5, with the modded 10-way cable, to the "Connector to ES-3"
                    header on your units PCB (see Fig. 1).</li>
                <li class="- topic/li ">Ensure all connectors are seated fully and correctly.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Secure the ES-5 in your Eurorack case with the four provided screws.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Reconnect power to your Eurorack case.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li "> Have fun!</li>
            </ol></p>
    </conbody>
